description: From Latin systylos, from Ancient Greek σύστυλος (sústulos, “with columns standing close”) from σύν (sún, “with”) + στῦλος (stûlos, “column”): compare French systyle.

entries.meaning: (architecture) Having a space equal to two diameters or four modules between two columns; said of a portico or building.
(architecture) A systyle temple or other edifice.
